  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nanbu Holistic Community Development Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a joint effort between the Sichuan Haihui Poverty Alleviation Service Center and the Nanbu Rural Development Association to assist rural villages by applying Heifer&#x2019;s Value-Based Holistic Community Development model. It will provide 220 families in two villages of Fuli Township, Nanbu County, with high-quality beef cattle and sows, along with technical services and training on animal nutrition and feeding, disease control and grass planting. The trainings will ensure that recipient families will improve their animal management, nutrition level and income. Another 410 families will benefit from Passing on the Gift within five years. The project will also conduct a variety of training on self-help group development and management, sanitation and health, environmental protection and holistic community development to achieve community self-reliance.</narrative>
  </description>
